## Git Safety

See `.cursor/rules/git-workflow.mdc` for full workflow. Key points:
- Commit after each logical unit of work; explain WHY in messages
- Never accumulate >500 lines of uncommitted changes across >5 files
- COMMIT before structural changes (renaming tabs, changing models, reorganizing files)
- Build-verify between phases of multi-file changes

---

## Secrets Safety

- NEVER hardcode API keys, passwords, or tokens in code
- NEVER use fallback values for secrets: `process.env.KEY || 'default-value'`
- NEVER run: `cat .env`, `echo $SECRET`
- ALWAYS use environment variables or secrets management
- ALWAYS add secret files to `.gitignore` BEFORE creating them

---

## Documentation

- Fixes and patches go in `[YOUR_SESSION_LOG_FILE].md` (append at top, never delete old entries)
- Substantial new features get their own `docs/` file + session log entry
- NEVER create standalone fix docs (`*_FIX.md`, `*_SUMMARY.md`, `*_COMPLETE.md`)

